## Layer 1: Single-Cell RNA-seq Analysis (GSE252470)

### 1.1 Load Raw 10x Genomics Data

Each sample requires three files: `barcodes.tsv`, `features.tsv`, `matrix.mtx`
organised in per-sample subfolders.

```{r load-scrna, eval=FALSE}
sample_ids <- c("N1_1", "N1_2", "N2_1", "N2_2", "N3", "N4", "N5", "N6")

# Load all 8 samples using ReadMtx (handles uncompressed files)
seurat_list <- lapply(sample_ids, function(sid) {
  counts <- ReadMtx(
    mtx      = file.path(sid, "matrix.mtx"),
    cells    = file.path(sid, "barcodes.tsv"),
    features = file.path(sid, "features.tsv")
  )
  CreateSeuratObject(counts,
                     project      = sid,
                     min.cells    = 3,
                     min.features = 200)
})
names(seurat_list) <- sample_ids

# Merge all samples
merged <- merge(seurat_list[[1]],
                y            = seurat_list[-1],
                add.cell.ids = sample_ids)
```

### 1.2 Quality Control

Three QC metrics are calculated per cell:
- `nFeature_RNA`: number of detected genes (low = empty droplet, high = doublet)
- `nCount_RNA`: total RNA molecules (extreme values = doublets)
- `percent.mt`: mitochondrial gene percentage (high = dying cell)

```{r qc, eval=FALSE}
merged[["percent.mt"]] <- PercentageFeatureSet(merged, pattern = "^MT-")

# Visualise QC metrics
VlnPlot(merged,
        features = c("nFeature_RNA", "nCount_RNA", "percent.mt"),
        ncol     = 3,
        pt.size  = 0)

# Filter low quality cells
merged_filtered <- subset(merged,
                           subset = nFeature_RNA > 200  &
                                    nFeature_RNA < 6000 &
                                    nCount_RNA   < 50000 &
                                    percent.mt   < 25)

cat("Cells after QC:", ncol(merged_filtered), "\n")
# Result: 47,078 cells retained from 57,685 raw cells
```

### 1.3 Seurat Preprocessing Pipeline

```{r preprocessing, eval=FALSE}
merged_filtered <- merged_filtered %>%
  NormalizeData() %>%
  FindVariableFeatures(nfeatures = 3000) %>%
  ScaleData() %>%
  RunPCA(npcs = 30) %>%
  FindNeighbors(dims = 1:20) %>%
  FindClusters(resolution = 0.5) %>%
  RunUMAP(dims = 1:20)
```

### 1.4 Cell Type Annotation

Clusters were annotated using canonical marker genes:

| Marker | Cell Type |
|--------|-----------|
| CD3E | T cells |
| CD79A | B cells |
| CD68, LYZ | Macrophages |
| CTSK, ACP5 | Osteoclasts |
| FAP, DCN | CAFs |
| PECAM1 | Endothelial |
| RUNX2, SPP1 | Osteoblasts/Tumor |

```{r annotation, eval=FALSE}
# Load pre-processed annotated object
merged_filtered <- readRDS("GSE252470_annotated.rds")

# Visualise cell type marker expression
DotPlot(merged_filtered,
        features  = c("PTPRC", "CD3E", "CD79A",
                       "CD68", "LYZ", "CTSK", "ACP5",
                       "FAP", "DCN", "PECAM1",
                       "RUNX2", "SPP1", "SRGN"),
        group.by  = "seurat_clusters",
        cols      = c("lightgrey", "darkred"),
        dot.scale = 6) +
