## Summary of Key Findings

| Analysis | n | Key Result | Statistic |
|---|---|---|---|
| scRNA-seq cell type | 47,078 cells | SRGN enriched in osteoclasts | χ²=5399.9, p<2.2e-16 |
| Bulk RNA-seq correlation | 198 dogs | SRGN ~ CTSK (R=0.22) | p=0.0019 |
| Bulk RNA-seq correlation | 198 dogs | SRGN ~ CD68 (R=0.23) | p=0.0013 |
| Canine survival | 97 dogs | No OS association | p=0.94 |
| Human recurrence | 37 patients | No recurrence association | p=0.72 |
| TF regulon (VIPER) | 4,047 osteoclasts | FOSL2, CEBPA, STAT5B enriched | FDR<10⁻¹³⁰ |

### Biological Interpretation

SRGN defines an osteoclast-enriched stromal compartment in canine OSA.
Its expression is driven by AP-1 (FOSL2), myeloid differentiation (CEBPA),
and JAK/STAT (STAT5B) transcription factors — a conserved regulatory axis
consistent with known SRGN biology in human cancers.
SRGN does not independently predict survival in bulk RNA-seq,
suggesting its role is mechanistic (bone destruction, ECM remodeling)
rather than prognostic at the population level.

